> What’s oh-so-nice, with a little spice? These hearty steak tacos! They’re filled to bursting with tender steak and red onion seasoned with our bold Mexican spice blend. Top your tacos with a quick homemade mango and jalapeño salsa (choose your own heat level!), then add dollops of tangy sour cream just before serving. Now we know you’re already sold, but there’s more: You’re only going to need one pan, and you’ll be ready to eat in a speedy 15 minutes!

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 1 TBSP
(2 TBSP for 4 servings). Drain @mango{4%ounce}. Dice @tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Mince
@jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat if desired.

Pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and thinly slice against the grain.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add
steak, sliced onion, and @Mexican spice blend{1%tablespoon} to pan; season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is softened and steak is cooked
to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine drained mango, tomato, minced onion,
@red wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and as much jalapeño as you like. Season with salt and
pepper to taste.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until warmed through,
~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with steak mixture. Top tacos with mango
salsa (draining first) and @sour cream{3%tablespoon}. Serve.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.